{"cursor":"4156","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n'Commerce' is the whole system of an economy that constitutes an environment for\nbusiness. The system includes legal, economic, political, social, cultural and\ntechnological systems that are in operation in any country. Thus, commerce is a\nsystem or an environment that affects the business prospects of an economy or a\nnation-state. It can also be defined as a component of business which includes\nall activities, functions and institutions involved in transferring goods from\nproducers to consumer.\n","linknr":166,"url":"Commerce","recorded":1362371965,"links":28,"instances":["economics","business_writer","business","economics","business"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Commerce|"],"headings":["History","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/57/Caduceus.svg/100px-Caduceus.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Emblem-money.svg/28px-Emblem-money.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["peter_watson","business_writer"],["barter","economics"],["product","business"],["service","economics"],["distribution","business"]],"members":["barter","peter_watson","product","service","distribution"],"related":["Communication","Prehistoric","Self-sufficiency","Trade","Barter","Peter_Watson_(business_writer)","History_of_international_trade","Circa","Currency","Money","Numismatist","Coin","Precious_metal","Gold","Barter_(economics)","Double_coincidence_of_wants","Corporation","Product_(business)","Service_(economics)","Market","Production_cost","International_trade","Tariff","F